23/09/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia- Montenegro -- The Serbia-Montenegro Defence Ministry confirmed Monday (22 September) that an army officer has been arrested on espionage charges. 
Lieutenant Colonel Dragoljub Zivkovic was arrested on charges of collecting military information and presenting himself as a security service member. 
According to Belgrade-based Radio B92, he gave the information to Russia. 
(B92, Tanjug, FoNet, BBC - 22/09/03)
